'''Sa<U+00EF>dou Simpor<U+00E9>''' is a [[Burkina Faso]] professional [[association football|footballer]], who plays as a [[Defender (association football)|Defender]] for [[Rail Club du Kadiogo]] and the [[Burkina Faso national football team]].<ref name="gsddf">{{cite web | url=http://www.mtnfootball.com/m/africa/african-tournaments/chan/team-profiles/2014/burkina-faso.html?Tab=squad | title=2014 CHAN - Burkina Faso Team Profile | publisher=mtnfootball.com/m | accessdate=13 March 2014}}</ref><ref name="bjjs">{{cite web | url=http://www.cafonline.com/userfiles/file/CHAN%202014%20TEAM%20LISTS%20/Burkina%20Faso.pdf | title=Squad List for BFA-T0006 Burkina Faso Burkina Faso | publisher=cafonline.com | accessdate=13 March 2014}}</ref>

==International career==
In January 2014, coach [[Brama Traore]], invited him to be a part of the [[Burkina Faso national football team|Burkina Faso]] squad for the [[2014 African Nations Championship]].<ref name="kfchj">{{cite web | url=http://www.modernghana.com/sports/512205/2/chan-2014-the-23-man-squad-of-burkina-faso.html | title=CHAN 2014: the 23-man squad of Burkina Faso | publisher=modernghana.com | accessdate=13 March 2014}}</ref><ref name="jjj">{{cite web | url=http://allsports.com.gh/2014/01/06/chan-2014-preview-group-b/ | title=CHAN 2014 Preview: GROUP B | publisher=allsports.com.gh | accessdate=13 March 2014}}</ref> The team was eliminated in the group stages after losing to  [[Uganda national football team|Uganda]] and [[Zimbabwe national football team|Zimbabwe]] and then drawing with [[Morocco national football team|Morocco]].<ref name="8itg9oui">{{cite web | url=http://allafrica.com/stories/201401161550.html | title=Burkina Faso/Morocco: Chan 2014 - Burkina Faso Vs Morocco, the Big Shock of the Day | publisher=allafrica.com | accessdate=13 March 2014}}</ref><ref name="gm">{{cite web | url=http://www.cafonline.com/competition/african-nations-championship_2014/news/19200-chan-2014-live-result-burkina-faso-0--1-zimbabwe.html | title=CHAN 2014: Final Result: Burkina Faso 0 - 1 Zimbabwe | publisher=cafonline.com/ | accessdate=13 March 2014}}</ref>

